Track Changes to Files in Globus (AWS) In the Change History
Automatically import data payloads from DataSpace

comments.body:
- [ ] Utilize https://dataspace.princeton.edu/rest//handle/<handle with a slash from ark> to get at the ID 

- [ ] then utilize https://dataspace.princeton.edu/rest/rest/items/<id>/bitstreams to download the actual data files https://wiki.lyrasis.org/display/DSDOC5x/REST+API#RESTAPI-Bitstreams. 

- [ ] Then utilize the retrieval link to get the data for each one. 

- [ ] To make things more complicated there is also data in Globus, which can be found utilizing a URI that includes globus from https://dataspace.princeton.edu/rest/items/<id>/metadata

princeton_ansible.title: Test Tower deploy on DACS projects

comments.body:
Max's wish list, based on this experience:
* That the Tower output updated - sometimes I see the success in the channel before I can see it in Tower.
* That the deploys went into their own channel, rather than the general server-alerts channel
* That it were easier in Tower to see the most relevant info for these jobs - that is, the project, branch, and environment.
* A way to link to specific output in Tower, especially standard error
These deploys have all been tested on staging.

comments.body: Overlaying the existing data isn't straightforward. The Drupal Node ID is the only possible overlay key for existing databases in the Drupal site. This is stored in the friendly_url in guides. We aren't assigning friendly_urls to new databases in guides. If we use this as match point we will need to make sure guide DB managers follow this practice.
